Sure, here are some example sentences using the Serbian word "bola":

1. *Bola* me glava celo jutro. (My head *hurts* all morning.)
2. Žao mi je što te *bola* stomak. (I'm sorry your stomach *hurts*.)
3. *Bola* ga ruka od preteranog korišćenja miša. (His arm *aches* from excessive mouse use.)
4. Prošle noći *bola* me zub i nisam mogao da spavam. (Last night my tooth *hurt* and I couldn't sleep.)
5. Ako te *bola* grlo, popij malo toplog čaja. (If your throat *hurts*, have some warm tea.)
6. Često *boli* leđa nakon dugog sedenja u kancelariji. (Back pain often *occurs* after sitting for a long time in the office.)
7. Ova igra *boli* oči, ne mogu da je gledam. (This game *hurts* my eyes, I can't watch it.)
8. Nemoj da me *boli* glava, već mi reci šta se desilo. (Don't give me a *headache*, just tell me what happened.)
9. Nažalost, mnoge stvari u životu nas *bole*. (Unfortunately, many things in life *hurt* us.)
10. Radujem se novoj knjizi koja će izaći jer sam veliki *fan bolo* književnosti. (I'm looking forward to the new book coming out because I'm a big *fan of mystery* literature.)

I hope these examples help!